-- Hong Kong's BEA kicks off earnings with 6 pct rise in H1 profit
-- By Saikat Chatterjee
-- Fri Aug 01, 2014 12:33AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 1 (Reuters) - The first of Hong Kong's banks kicked off earnings on Friday with Bank of East Asia Ltd <0023.HK> posting a slight rise in quarterly profit as investors focused on the sector's strengthening ties with China and the risks that could pose.

Bank of East Asia reported a 6 percent gain in first-half net profit, and said it expected its business operating environment to remain uncertain in the second half.